<big><math>\Longrightarrow</math><math>\lfloor</math><span style="font-family:Quintessential;">'''''Level 77''' is the '''78<sup>th</sup>''' level of '''[[The Backrooms]]'''.''</span>'''''<math>\rceil</math>'''''<math>\Longleftarrow</math></big>

<div class="styled-quote">{{Quote|A long journey rests ahead of you and a beautiful yet twisted path lies at your feet. All the more welcoming is the storm set over the dampened horizon. Life feels like it could not get easier, like watching the stars aimlessly drift bold night sky. True peace is the reward for such a life; simply feeling fulfilled, nothing more that can be done or should be done. Acceptance is key for not every wicked or cruel thing in this should hide the elegance of such a fate.|A True Friend}}</div>

==<math>\Longrightarrow</math><math>\lfloor</math><span style="color: #FFFFFF; text-shadow: 2px 1px 0 #454545;"><span style="font-family:Quintessential;">Depiction</span></span><math>\rceil</math><math>\Longleftarrow</math>==
<div style="font-family:Times New Roman;">
<div class="right-image2">
[[File:77Fate.png|Beauty at its finest hour.]]
<span style="font-family:Quintessential;">A depiction of what one will observe after accepting fate.</span>
</div>
'''Level 77''' is a dismal landscape of ranches and fields shrouded in thick, overhanging fog. They are imperfect and broken, leaving only smudges of sense in what is or has been. The level emits an ominous feeling, causing dread and tension among wanderers who enter it. Small fields filled with rusting farming equipment can be seen throughout the lonely plains. Weary stables rest their aged skeletons in the center of the floor; they can barely stand after what they've been through.

The general temperature of '''Level 77''' is ''58°F (14°C)'' with a constant cool breeze. '''Level 77''' is mostly stuck in mild rain, with thunder rumbling across the abandoned fields. Time is irrelevant here; the light has led most people to believe it is late afternoon, almost evening. The storm ahead is ready to break. The size is unknown, but walking in any direction will eventually take you back to the crippled ranch.

The lifeless ranch of '''Level 77''' appears to have been a functional ranch at one point, but time has gotten the best of it. The presence of rusted equipment, such as rusting tractors and damaged tools, suggests this. There is simply a one-person dilapidated house and a horse stable. The interiors of both towers are dusty but not decaying.

The rest of the interiors are disheveled, giving the impression that they were raided by an unknown entity. The house is now more of a skeleton of its former self, with only a log structure that may be restored with the proper effort. The stable, however, is where most people live because it gives better protection from the approaching storm.

<div class="right-image2">
[[File:77New.png|Is it beauty, though?]]
<span style="font-family:Quintessential;">A section of '''Level 77''' with foggy mist and endless rivers. This is a picture taken by an anonymous wanderer who accepted fate 90 minutes ago.</span>
</div>
Anyone unlucky enough to find themselves in '''Level 77''' is not doomed; instead, they will have to approach life with a new perspective. One must learn how to be alive here till one discovers an exit. Nobody can see each other; everyone to his own. Crops cannot be propagated here because of the constant storms that pollute the soil.

Hunger is not the cause of death; it is age or a lack of water. It is best to simply accept this nightmare and live it as if running through the stars. The plains will begin to move to accommodate their new owner: a fresh soul eager to live life as it should be.

<small><span style="font-family:Quintessential;"><center><math>\Longrightarrow</math><math>\lfloor</math><big>''Death is not eternal, but death can happen at any time.<math>\rceil</math><math>\Longleftarrow</math>''</big></center></span></small>


Statues of famous people who have had a significant impact on modern society are also claimed to be found in the fields. Each statue is a tribute to humanity's harsh past. Statues can be found in relatively pristine condition, with only the occasional smudge or lone vine smearing their elegant image. Look up to them as leaders, guides who will cheer you on throughout your life. It is possible to see statues of people of no historical significance, ruining the statues' historical elegance. Each with the best thing they have ever said in their life. '''Level 77''' contains tons of these statues, like it represents a graveyard.

<span style="font-family:Quintessential;"><center><math>\Longrightarrow</math><math>\lfloor</math><big>''Survive through the stormy fields of entropy and leave with a life worth living.<math>\rceil</math><math>\Longleftarrow</math>''</big></center></span>

==<math>\Longrightarrow</math><math>\lfloor</math><span style="color: #FFFFFF; text-shadow: 2px 1px 0 #454545;"><span style="font-family:Quintessential;">The Farm</span></span><math>\rceil</math><math>\Longleftarrow</math>==
<div class="right-image2">
[[File:77Farm.png|Welcome to the farm.]]
<span style="font-family:Quintessential;">A drone view of '''Level 77's''' farm. The wanderer has fallen to the fog effect in '''Level 77'''.</span>
</div>
'''Level 77's''' farm normally sits isolated, far away from any lakes, forests, or fields filled with roses and trees. It sits on muddy plains with a bright yellow beige-like fog, with visibility rarely extending beyond 10 to 40 feet. The farmhouse itself is run-down and on the verge of collapse, built of dark, damp wood with sagging roofs and shattered windows.

Rusted tractors and damaged farming tools would be scattered across the fields, partially sunken in mud from years of heavy, constant rain. Thin puddles of water would reflect the pale sky, as dead grass bends endlessly in the wind. There would be no animals on the land, not even insects or birds, resulting in an unnatural silence interrupted only by distant thunder and creaking wood.

Strange stone statues would appear at random places in the fields near the farm. Some resemble faceless farmers, while others are eroded beyond recognition. Wanderers would notice statues changing places subtly as thick fog rolled across the land. Despite this, the statues never directly attack anyone; instead, they observe in silence.

<div class="right-image2">
[[File:77RosesFarm.png|So, what do you think?]]
<span style="font-family:Quintessential;">A closeup of '''Level 77's''' farm. Roses can be seen everywhere.</span>
</div>

The atmosphere would always feel like a late afternoon, just before nightfall. A warm yellow mist would glow faintly beyond the horizon, giving the landscape a strangely eerie appearance, like old faded photographs. Rain would fall lightly for hours before suddenly stopping, leaving only dense fog and distant storm clouds.

The barn is the safest structure. Inside, there are dusty horse stalls, moldy hay, and hanging lamps that can light themselves during storms. The farmhouse interior represents '''[[Level 116]]''' but appears to have been raided and left empty, with overturned furniture, muddy footprints leading nowhere, and water dripping from the roof even after the rain has stopped outside.

A rusting well would sit in the center of the farm, surrounded by dead flowers and scorched grass. Looking into it reveals only dense fog, not water. According to scattered notes left around the farm, climbing into the well is one of the few known ways out, although many visitors become emotionally attached to the farm before attempting to leave.

==<math>\Longrightarrow</math><math>\lfloor</math><span style="color: #FFFFFF; text-shadow: 2px 1px 0 #454545;"><span style="font-family:Quintessential;">The Graveyard</span></span><math>\rceil</math><math>\Longleftarrow</math>==
<div class="right-image2">
[[File:ThisisNOTAIThiswastakenfromadobeandeditedandmodifiedbyme.png|THE GRAVEYARD SHIFT]]
<span style="font-family:Quintessential;">The foggy graveyard of '''Level 77'''.</span>
</div>
'''Level 77's''' graveyard stretches endlessly across a swampy forest beneath a constant yellow-beige fog. Unlike normal cemeteries, the graves are not arranged in rows. Tombstones would appear randomly throughout the muddy landscape like they were rising from the earth, or what's called '''Level 77'''.

Pools of stagnant water form between graves, reflecting weird and faint shapes that disappear when looked at. Ancient leafless trees rise above the graveyard, their branches twisting together like tangled veins. The fog stays very low, often barely a few feet above the ground, making far-away graves disappear into darkness.

Wanderers report hearing faint whispers carried by the wind, but no voices have yet been identified. The atmosphere is depressing and dark, and emotionally exhausting, creating a constant sensation of grief and nostalgia. Many gravestones contain names that do not exist in any known records. Some have no writing at all, while others have inscriptions that change each time they are looked at. Despite there being no people in '''Level 77''', a few graves looked to have been freshly dug. Rusted fences and collapsed tombs emerge from the fog before disappearing during storms, making the layout impossible to accurately map.

In the center of the cemetery stands a massive crimson tree, surrounded by dead flowers and blackened grass. Its leaves never fall, even during violent winds. A shattered stone angel statue with a missing face lies beneath the tree. Wanderers who spend days, weeks, or even years near the tree come to hear distant church bells, despite the fact that there is no church on '''Level 77'''. The angel can talk and respond to anything the wanderer says. The angel has a missing hand, a damaged face, and a ripped wing. If you ever mention about '''[[Level 80]]''', [[The Void|'''''the angel will not be happy..''''']]

==<math>\Longrightarrow</math><math>\lfloor</math><span style="color: #FFFFFF; text-shadow: 2px 1px 0 #454545;"><span style="font-family:Quintessential;">Accompaniment</span></span><math>\rceil</math><math>\Longleftarrow</math>==

One will find oneself entirely alone, without a single soul to ease the pain. Not even a coyote to give a sense of purpose; nothing to guard. It is only one with their brutal thoughts about what life should be. No entities such as [[Entity 3|Smilers]] or [[Entity 10|Skin-Stealers]] will come to end a poor soul waiting. One is the sole caretaker of their new life; no help will anyone receive.

The only company one will receive is the statues. The statues that guide one to greatness and peace, to a better place. Life is too rambunctious with all of the strife in the world. '''Level 77''' takes all of that pain and suffering away.
