<div class="blurquote-noperson blurquote-noborder" style="margin:1em;">
{{Blurquote|image=C2CEA29F-865F-4479-93BE-B3E112D78861.jpeg|quote-text=
I woke up in this desolate, derelict field, like a lone star, standing out in a dark, inky sky . . .
And there stood the statues, tall stony giants, mocking my suffering in their silent disposition, as if to communicate their silent wisdom in their penetrating gaze . . .
And there was the farm, the land that must remain in its solitude and desiccation, for those are the only things that give this place meaning, the only things that make it unique among so many others . . .
And there were the trees, eternally rooted to the ground that sustains it, for these ancient giants in all of their natural wisdom are only really pawns in a game played by God . . .
And there was the wind, howling in my ears, with all of its natural fluidity and elegance, whispering to me, showing me just how far I've come as I stand on the cliff, gazing upon the solitary vista . . .
And there was the Storm, a herald of coming disaster, the harbinger of the brink of demise, the signal of a fate long awaited . . .
Heaven lay in those clouds . . .
But here I was in a subjective hell of my own making . . .
}}</div></div></div></div>

